Mazi Sam Ohuabunwa, a presidential aspirant on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has expressed support for consensus arrangement for the nomination of a presidential candidate of the party, hoping the best aspirant will be chosen.
Ohuabunwa at the Kwara State PDP Secretariat, Ilorin, emphasized that only people who do not want good for Nigeria will ignore an opportunity to produce the best candidate through consensus.
Mazi Ohuabunwa maintained that it won’t be rational to oppose consensus candidate, reiterating that the best must emerge for the PDP to have a chance to win the 2023 presidential election.
The presidential aspirant promised to make Nigeria an investment destination, create employment opportunities and wipe out poverty.
